' Usage Flow
note as UsageNote
  **Usage (Identical Everywhere)**
  
  ```typescript
  // Import ONCE singleton accessor
  import { ONCE } from '@web4x/once';
  
  // In Node.js
  const kernel = await ONCE.start(scenario);
  
  // In Browser
  const kernel = await ONCE.start(scenario);
  
  // In Worker
  const kernel = await ONCE.start(scenario);
  
  // Always returns OnceKernel interface
  const health = await kernel.getHealth();
  const result = await kernel.invokeMethod('getPeers', {});
  
  // Access global singleton
  const instance = ONCE.getInstance();
  ```
end note

' Environment Detection Flow
note as DetectionFlow
  **Environment Detection Logic**
  
  1. Check typeof process !== 'undefined'
     → if process.versions.node: Node.js → NodeJsOnce
  
  2. Check typeof self !== 'undefined'
     → if ServiceWorkerGlobalScope: Service Worker → ServiceWorkerOnce
     → if DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: Web Worker → WorkerOnce
  
  3. Check typeof window !== 'undefined'
     → Check window.matchMedia('(display-mode: standalone)')
       → if true: PWA → BrowserOnce (PWA mode)
     → Check window !== window.parent
       → if true: iFrame → BrowserOnce (iframe mode)
     → else: Browser → BrowserOnce
  
  4. Fallback: Browser → BrowserOnce
  
  Return appropriate kernel instance
end note

